assets.description: I made this as I was researching the PSVR and Google Tilt Brush as a means to generate 3D adn VR content. It was a rather quick play around, and I started with the smoke brush applied to a spherical guide. Then I dropped that idea and just drew the arms of the galaxy spreading out from the center. Used a fw different shades of blue. really happy with this so far. Next I would love to have more finer details being applied to the smoke.

assets.description: More play and practice with working in scales. If you want to experience this scene in VR, give it a Like and view it in your Liked Scenes in Tilt Brush. You can then resize the scene so you’re at human height and stand on the flatter rocks (there’s three of them in the scene) to view Getaway from the angles it was sculpted in.
